parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the LCM can cause the headlights, taillights, and brake lights to malfunction or fail, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Headlights and taillights may not turn on
or may be dim; brake lights may not function; lights may not respond to the switch; difficulty seeing at night; increased risk of accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the LCM can cause the headlights, taillights, and interior lights to malfunction or fail, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Headlights and taillights fail to turn on or turn off intermittently
and the vehicle may experience electrical system failures.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
and may not respond to braking attempts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause a range of problems, including loss of power, reduced visibility, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences electrical system failures

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, making it challenging to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels stiff or hard to turn
the steering wheel binds or seizes
the steering wheel does not return to its normal position
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the steering wheel feels like it's going to come off.
